attributes.description: Overview of Cisco Meraki Device Health metrics

query.esql:
from metrics-cisco_meraki_metrics.device_health-* 
| keep meraki.device.serial, meraki.device.license.expiration_date 
| where meraki.device.license.expiration_date is not null 
| stats expiration_date=max(meraki.device.license.expiration_date) by meraki.device.serial 
| sort expiration_date desc 
| rename meraki.device.serial AS `Device Serial`, expiration_date AS `Expiration Date`

from metrics-cisco_meraki_metrics.device_health-* 
| keep meraki.device.serial, meraki.device.license.expiration_date 
| where meraki.device.license.expiration_date is not null 
| stats expiration_date=max(meraki.device.license.expiration_date) by meraki.device.serial 
| sort expiration_date desc 
| rename meraki.device.serial AS `Device Serial`, expiration_date AS `Expiration Date`

from metrics-cisco_meraki_metrics.device_health-* 
| keep meraki.switch.port.status.client_count, meraki.switch.port.status.duplex, meraki.switch.port.status.enabled, meraki.switch.port.status.is_uplink, meraki.switch.port.status.power_usage_in_wh, meraki.switch.port.status.speed, meraki.switch.port.status.status, meraki.switch.port.status.stp_statuses
| where meraki.switch.port.status.client_count is not null 
| stats client_count=max(meraki.switch.port.status.client_count) by meraki.switch.port.status.duplex, meraki.switch.port.status.enabled, meraki.switch.port.status.is_uplink, meraki.switch.port.status.power_usage_in_wh, meraki.switch.port.status.speed, meraki.switch.port.status.status, meraki.switch.port.status.stp_statuses
| sort client_count desc 
| rename client_count as `Client Count`, meraki.switch.port.status.duplex as Duplex, meraki.switch.port.status.enabled as Enabled, meraki.switch.port.status.is_uplink as `Is Uplink`, meraki.switch.port.status.power_usage_in_wh as `Power Usage (Wh)`, meraki.switch.port.status.speed as Speed, meraki.switch.port.status.status as Status, meraki.switch.port.status.stp_statuses as `STP Status`

from metrics-cisco_meraki_metrics.device_health-* 
| keep meraki.switch.port.status.client_count, meraki.switch.port.status.duplex, meraki.switch.port.status.enabled, meraki.switch.port.status.is_uplink, meraki.switch.port.status.power_usage_in_wh, meraki.switch.port.status.speed, meraki.switch.port.status.status, meraki.switch.port.status.stp_statuses
| where meraki.switch.port.status.client_count is not null 
| stats client_count=max(meraki.switch.port.status.client_count) by meraki.switch.port.status.duplex, meraki.switch.port.status.enabled, meraki.switch.port.status.is_uplink, meraki.switch.port.status.power_usage_in_wh, meraki.switch.port.status.speed, meraki.switch.port.status.status, meraki.switch.port.status.stp_statuses
| sort client_count desc 
| rename client_count as `Client Count`, meraki.switch.port.status.duplex as Duplex, meraki.switch.port.status.enabled as Enabled, meraki.switch.port.status.is_uplink as `Is Uplink`, meraki.switch.port.status.power_usage_in_wh as `Power Usage (Wh)`, meraki.switch.port.status.speed as Speed, meraki.switch.port.status.status as Status, meraki.switch.port.status.stp_statuses as `STP Status`
